newBehaviorSec

public BehaviorSec newBehaviorSec()
                           throws METSException
Return an empty BehaviorSec. The returned object has no properties or content and is not part of the METS document, it is essentially a constructor of a METS element which is owned by the METS document. The returned object needs to be "filled out" (e.g. with id, additional sub-elements, etc) before being added to the METS document.

Throws:
METSException
